      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: scope skill slugs by owner",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nMake skill slug handling owner-aware across ClawHub while preserving legacy slug-only compatibility where the public v1 API still cannot encode an owner namespace.\n\nThis PR keeps the platform invariant explicit: skill slugs are unique per publisher namespace, not globally. First-class publish/update/install flows now carry owner context, while legacy reads either resolve deterministically through the compatibility helper or return a controlled ambiguity response.\n\n## What changed\n\n- Adds owner-aware skill/alias lookup helpers in `convex/lib/skills/slugResolution.ts`.\n- Updates publish/versioning paths to resolve existing skills by owner namespace, including migration/source-owner handling.\n- Updates slug availability, package fallback, downloads, telemetry, security scan, moderation-adjacent reads, backups, and public read paths away from unsafe global `.unique()` assumptions.\n- Adds structured ambiguous slug responses for slug-only v1 read/install surfaces.\n- Keeps legacy slug-only compatibility by preferring the `openclaw` publisher when duplicate slug matches exist there, otherwise returning controlled ambiguity instead of crashing.\n- Updates ClawHub CLI surfaces to support `@owner/slug`, persist owner metadata, and default publish owner to `/api/v1/whoami` when `--owner` is omitted.\n- Updates UI/docs install examples to use `@owner/slug` where the owner handle is known.\n\n## Compatibility decisions\n\n- We did **not** make `/api/v1/skills/<slug>` require owner context because v1 URLs cannot encode owner without breaking existing clients.\n- We did **not** break old CLI publish clients. Omitted owner remains the legacy/personal publish behavior on the HTTP endpoint.\n- New ClawHub CLI publish does send owner context on the wire by defaulting to the authenticated user handle via `whoami`.\n- Slug-only legacy reads are intentionally still supported, but they now avoid global uniqueness crashes and make ambiguity explicit.\n\n## Follow-up / companion\n\n- OpenClaw CLI should get matching `@owner/slug` install/update UX so `openclaw skills install @owner/slug` handles ambiguous ClawHub slugs cleanly. I did not find an open matching OpenClaw PR while preparing this PR.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `AUTOREVIEW_AUTO_TESTS=0 .agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --reviewer codex --fallback-reviewer none`\n  - `autoreview clean: no accepted/actionable findings reported`\n- `bun run ci:unit`\n  - 237 test files passed\n  - 2613 tests passed\n- `bunx vitest run convex/skills.ownership.test.ts convex/packages.public.test.ts --reporter=dot`\n- `bun run format:check -- convex/skills.ts convex/skills.ownership.test.ts convex/packages.public.test.ts`\n- `bunx tsc --noEmit`\n",
        "branch": "pe/owner-scoped-skill-slugs",
